# Google Cloud Vision API OCR rules

## API endpoint (REST)
- Cloud Vision `images:annotate` endpoint:
  - `POST https://vision.googleapis.com/v1/images:annotate`
- Requests are JSON with a `requests` array, each item containing:
  - `image: { content }` where `content` is base64
  - `features: [{ type: "DOCUMENT_TEXT_DETECTION" }]`
- Batch up to 16 images per request.
- Include `x-goog-user-project` header for billing attribution.

## Authentication
- Use OAuth2 access tokens derived from a Service Account (server-to-server).
- In the Worker:
  - do NOT rely on interactive `gcloud` auth
  - do NOT bundle the entire service account JSON in source control
- Preferred approach:
  - Store service account JSON as a secret (`.dev.vars` locally, Wrangler secrets in prod)
  - Generate a signed JWT assertion and exchange it for an access token
  - Cache the access token until expiry (in-memory per isolate is fine for a POC)

## Output handling
- Extract `fullTextAnnotation.text` from each response item.
- Keep OCR output parsing minimal:
  - extract full text
  - optionally keep page/paragraph structure only if user needs it
- Normalize OCR text before sending to OpenAI:
  - strip obviously empty pages
  - limit max characters / tokens to avoid runaway OpenAI usage
  - include minimal metadata: filename, mimeType, page count if available

## Error handling
- Treat upstream errors distinctly:
  - Auth error (401/403) -> map to 502 with `UPSTREAM_AUTH_FAILED`
  - Vision API validation (400) -> map to 400 with `INVALID_DOCUMENT`
  - Rate/Quota (429) -> map to 503 with `UPSTREAM_RATE_LIMITED`
  - Other 5xx -> map to 502 with `UPSTREAM_ERROR`
